<project>
	<name>Gentoo PPC64</name>
		<longname>Gentoo Linux PPC64 Development</longname>
		<date>January 30, 2005</date>

	<description>
		The PPC64 Development Project is devoted to keeping Gentoo in
		good shape on the PowerPC64 architecture.
	</description>

	<longdescription>
		<p>This project is dedicated to running Gentoo on PowerPC64
		systems. These systems encompass IBM RS/6000s, Power Macintosh G5
		systems, IBM pSeries and soon IBM iSeries boxen.</p>
	</longdescription>

	<extrachapter position="top">
		<title>News</title>
			<section>
				<title>2005-01-30: Please move to cascarding
				profiles</title>
			<body>
				<p>Please move to cascarding profile. You need portage-2.0.51-r*. This
				can be done following this steps. (An up-to-date portage tree is
				obligatory)</p>

				<pre>
rm -f /etc/make.profile
cd /etc
ln -s /usr/portage/profiles/default-linux/ppc64/2004.3 make.profile
				</pre>
			</body>
		</section>
	
		<section>
			<title>2005-01-01: Project meeting</title>
			<body>
				<p>As a project, we're about a year old now. There are a number of
				packages not marked stable yet but over time we're improving. Gnome is
				starting to get close and kde is there. Hopefully this is useful and
				if you like please join us on irc.freenode.net #gentoo-ppc64.</p>

				<p>nigoro, corsair and tgall held a meeting on 01/01/2005 to discuss
				future items they intend to focus on. The list is:</p>

				<ul>
					<li>mozilla -- tgall_foo to check in nss fixes</li>
					<li>newer xorg support -- corsair / nigoro / tgall</li>
					<li>mga accel support in xorg -- tgall_foo</li>
					<li>cascading profiles -- tgall_foo  (done!)</li>
					<li>kde menu bug -- nigoro</li>
					<li>d.g.o/~tgall -> ppc64.gentoo.org -- corsair (done as you can
					see)</li>
				</ul>

				<p>The 2005.0 release was also discussed.  Look for lots of good things in
				the next few weeks.</p>

			</body>
		</section>
	</extrachapter>

